69.9	The_Fifth_Discipline	The Fifth Discipline	The Fifth Discipline: The Art and Practice of the Learning Organization is a book by Peter Senge (a senior lecturer at MIT) focusing on group problem solving using the systems thinking method in order to convert companies into learning organizations. The five disciplines represent approaches (theories and methods) for developing three core learning capabilities: fostering aspiration, developing reflective conversation, and understanding complexity.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/31/The_fifth_discipline_cover.jpg/200px-The_fifth_discipline_cover.jpg
